      "message": "1. it is slightly different operation, replaceListElement reconciles elements of one list \nFor Example in the follwoing structure, with parent xpath /bookstore[@name\u003dEasons] and data in DB as:\n\nbookstore[name\u003dEasons]\n - categoies[code\u003dkids]\n - categories[code\u003dthriller]\n - staff[id\u003dalice]\n - premises\n\nIf I am trying to replace [kids, thriller] with [horror, comedy] and staff[] then,\nA replaceListContent takes first payload element \u0027categories[horror]\u0027 and derives the list prefix as \u0027/categories[\u0027 and reconciles only that list and only changes [kids, thriller] to [horror, comedy]. \nHere staff and premises remain unchanged.\nThis is because we find first child node xpath prefix inside getListElementXpathPrefix()\n\nreplaceAllChildDataNodes reconciles every direct child of parent node bookstore. That is it replaces [kids, thriller] and deletes staff and premises.\n\nSo difference is in scope not orphan handling. Both delete orphans, just that the new one is not limited to one list element.",
